96static void
97readcb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)
98{
99 if (evbuffer_get_length(bev->input) == 8333) {
100 struct evbuffer *evbuf = evbuffer_new();
101 assert(evbuf != NULL);
102
103 /* gratuitous test of bufferevent_read_buffer */
104 bufferevent_read_buffer(bev, evbuf);
105
106 bufferevent_disable(bev, EV_READ);
107
108 if (evbuffer_get_length(evbuf) == 8333) {
109 test_ok++;
110 }
111
112 evbuffer_free(evbuf);
113 }
114}
115
116static void
117writecb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)
118{
119 if (evbuffer_get_length(bev->output) == 0) {
120 test_ok++;
121 }
122}

125errorcb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *arg)
126{
127 test_ok = -2;

130static void
131test_bufferevent_impl(int use_pair, int flush)
132{
133 struct bufferevent *bev1 = NULL, *bev2 = NULL;
134 char buffer[8333];
135 int i;
136 int expected = 2;
137
138 if (use_pair) {
139 struct bufferevent *xpair[2];
140 tt_assert(0 == bufferevent_pair_new(NULL, 0, xpair));
141 bev1 = xpair[0];
142 bev2 = xpair[1];
143 bufferevent_setcb(bev1, readcb, writecb, errorcb, bev1);
144 bufferevent_setcb(bev2, readcb, writecb, errorcb, NULL);
145 tt_int_op(bufferevent_getfd(bev1), ==, -1);
146 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_get_underlying(bev1), ==, NULL);
147 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_pair_get_partner(bev1), ==, bev2);
148 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_pair_get_partner(bev2), ==, bev1);
149 } else {
150 bev1 = bufferevent_new(pair[0], readcb, writecb, errorcb, NULL);
151 bev2 = bufferevent_new(pair[1], readcb, writecb, errorcb, NULL);
152 tt_int_op(bufferevent_getfd(bev1), ==, pair[0]);
153 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_get_underlying(bev1), ==, NULL);
154 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_pair_get_partner(bev1), ==, NULL);
155 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_pair_get_partner(bev2), ==, NULL);
156 }
157
158 {
159 /* Test getcb. */
160 bufferevent_data_cb r, w;
161 bufferevent_event_cb e;
162 void *a;
163 bufferevent_getcb(bev1, &r, &w, &e, &a);
164 tt_ptr_op(r, ==, readcb);
165 tt_ptr_op(w, ==, writecb);
166 tt_ptr_op(e, ==, errorcb);
167 tt_ptr_op(a, ==, use_pair ? bev1 : NULL);
168 }
169
170 bufferevent_disable(bev1, EV_READ);
171 bufferevent_enable(bev2, EV_READ);
172
173 tt_int_op(bufferevent_get_enabled(bev1), ==, EV_WRITE);
174 tt_int_op(bufferevent_get_enabled(bev2), ==, EV_WRITE|EV_READ);
175
176 for (i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(buffer); i++)
177 buffer[i] = i;
178
179 bufferevent_write(bev1, buffer, sizeof(buffer));
180 if (flush >= 0) {
181 tt_int_op(bufferevent_flush(bev1, EV_WRITE, flush), >=, 0);
182 }
183
184 event_dispatch();
185
186 bufferevent_free(bev2);
187 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_pair_get_partner(bev1), ==, NULL);
188 bufferevent_free(bev1);
189
190 /** Only pair call errorcb for BEV_FINISHED */
191 if (use_pair && flush == BEV_FINISHED) {
192 expected = -1;
193 }
194 if (test_ok != expected)
195 test_ok = 0;
196end:
197 ;
198}

211#if defined(EVTHREAD_USE_PTHREADS_IMPLEMENTED)
212/**
213 * Trace lock/unlock/alloc/free for locks.
214 * (More heavier then evthread_debug*)
215 */
216typedef struct
217{
218 void *lock;
219 enum {
220 ALLOC, FREE,
221 } status;
222 size_t locked /** allow recursive locking */;
223} lock_wrapper;
224struct lock_unlock_base
225{
226 /* Original callbacks */
227 struct evthread_lock_callbacks cbs;
228 /* Map of locks */
229 lock_wrapper *locks;
230 size_t nr_locks;
231} lu_base = {
232 .locks = NULL,
233};
234
235static lock_wrapper *lu_find(void *lock_)
236{
237 size_t i;
238 for (i = 0; i < lu_base.nr_locks; ++i) {
239 lock_wrapper *lock = &lu_base.locks[i];
240 if (lock->lock == lock_)
241 return lock;
242 }
243 return NULL;
244}
245
246static void *trace_lock_alloc(unsigned locktype)
247{
248 void *lock;
249 ++lu_base.nr_locks;
250 lu_base.locks = realloc(lu_base.locks,
251 sizeof(lock_wrapper) * lu_base.nr_locks);
252 lock = lu_base.cbs.alloc(locktype);
253 lu_base.locks[lu_base.nr_locks - 1] = (lock_wrapper){ lock, ALLOC, 0 };
254 return lock;
255}
256static void trace_lock_free(void *lock_, unsigned locktype)
257{
258 lock_wrapper *lock = lu_find(lock_);
259 if (!lock || lock->status == FREE || lock->locked) {
260 TT_FAIL(("lock: free error"));
261 } else {
262 lock->status = FREE;
263 lu_base.cbs.free(lock_, locktype);
264 }
265}
266static int trace_lock_lock(unsigned mode, void *lock_)
267{
268 lock_wrapper *lock = lu_find(lock_);
269 if (!lock || lock->status == FREE) {
270 TT_FAIL(("lock: lock error"));
271 return -1;
272 } else {
273 ++lock->locked;
274 return lu_base.cbs.lock(mode, lock_);
275 }
276}
277static int trace_lock_unlock(unsigned mode, void *lock_)
278{
279 lock_wrapper *lock = lu_find(lock_);
280 if (!lock || lock->status == FREE || !lock->locked) {
281 TT_FAIL(("lock: unlock error"));
282 return -1;
283 } else {
284 --lock->locked;
285 return lu_base.cbs.unlock(mode, lock_);
286 }
287}
288static void lock_unlock_free_thread_cbs(void)
289{
290 event_base_free(NULL);
291
292 if (libevent_tests_running_in_debug_mode)
293 libevent_global_shutdown();
294
295 /** drop immutable flag */
296 evthread_set_lock_callbacks(NULL);
297 /** avoid calling of event_global_setup_locks_() for new cbs */
298 libevent_global_shutdown();
299 /** drop immutable flag for non-debug ops (since called after shutdown) */
300 evthread_set_lock_callbacks(NULL);
301}
302
303static int use_lock_unlock_profiler(void)
304{
305 struct evthread_lock_callbacks cbs = {
306 EVTHREAD_LOCK_API_VERSION,
307 EVTHREAD_LOCKTYPE_RECURSIVE,
308 trace_lock_alloc,
309 trace_lock_free,
310 trace_lock_lock,
311 trace_lock_unlock,
312 };
313 memcpy(&lu_base.cbs, evthread_get_lock_callbacks(),
314 sizeof(lu_base.cbs));
315 {
316 lock_unlock_free_thread_cbs();
317
318 evthread_set_lock_callbacks(&cbs);
319 /** re-create debug locks correctly */
320 evthread_enable_lock_debugging();
321
322 event_init();
323 }
324 return 0;
325}
326static void free_lock_unlock_profiler(struct basic_test_data *data)
327{
328 /** fix "held_by" for kqueue */
329 evthread_set_lock_callbacks(NULL);
330
331 lock_unlock_free_thread_cbs();
332 free(lu_base.locks);
333 data->base = NULL;
334}

336static void test_bufferevent_pair_release_lock(void *arg)
337{
338 struct basic_test_data *data = arg;
339 use_lock_unlock_profiler();
340 {
341 struct bufferevent *xpair[2];
342 if (!bufferevent_pair_new(NULL, BEV_OPT_THREADSAFE, xpair)) {
343 bufferevent_free(xpair[0]);
344 bufferevent_free(xpair[1]);
345 } else
346 tt_abort_perror("bufferevent_pair_new");
347 }
348 free_lock_unlock_profiler(data);
349end:
350 ;
351}

358static void
359wm_readcb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)
360{
361 struct evbuffer *evbuf = evbuffer_new();
362 int len = (int)evbuffer_get_length(bev->input);
363 static int nread;
364
365 assert(len >= 10 && len <= 20);
366
367 assert(evbuf != NULL);
368
369 /* gratuitous test of bufferevent_read_buffer */
370 bufferevent_read_buffer(bev, evbuf);
371
372 nread += len;
373 if (nread == 65000) {
374 bufferevent_disable(bev, EV_READ);
375 test_ok++;
376 }
377
378 evbuffer_free(evbuf);
379}

382wm_writecb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)

385 if (evbuffer_get_length(bev->output) == 0) {
386 evbuffer_drain(bev->output, evbuffer_get_length(bev->output));
387 test_ok++;
388 }
389}

397static void
398test_bufferevent_watermarks_impl(int use_pair)
399{
400 struct bufferevent *bev1 = NULL, *bev2 = NULL;
401 char buffer[65000];
402 size_t low, high;
403 int i;
404 test_ok = 0;
405
406 if (use_pair) {
407 struct bufferevent *xpair[2];
408 tt_assert(0 == bufferevent_pair_new(NULL, 0, xpair));
409 bev1 = xpair[0];
410 bev2 = xpair[1];
411 bufferevent_setcb(bev1, NULL, wm_writecb, errorcb, NULL);
412 bufferevent_setcb(bev2, wm_readcb, NULL, errorcb, NULL);
413 } else {
414 bev1 = bufferevent_new(pair[0], NULL, wm_writecb, wm_errorcb, NULL);
415 bev2 = bufferevent_new(pair[1], wm_readcb, NULL, wm_errorcb, NULL);
416 }
417 tt_assert(bev1);
418 tt_assert(bev2);
419 bufferevent_disable(bev1, EV_READ);
420 bufferevent_enable(bev2, EV_READ);
421
422 /* By default, low watermarks are set to 0 */
423 bufferevent_getwatermark(bev1, EV_READ, &low, NULL);
424 tt_int_op(low, ==, 0);
425 bufferevent_getwatermark(bev2, EV_WRITE, &low, NULL);
426 tt_int_op(low, ==, 0);
427
428 for (i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(buffer); i++)
429 buffer[i] = (char)i;
430
431 /* limit the reading on the receiving bufferevent */
432 bufferevent_setwatermark(bev2, EV_READ, 10, 20);
433
434 bufferevent_getwatermark(bev2, EV_READ, &low, &high);
435 tt_int_op(low, ==, 10);
436 tt_int_op(high, ==, 20);
437
438 /* Tell the sending bufferevent not to notify us till it's down to
439 100 bytes. */
440 bufferevent_setwatermark(bev1, EV_WRITE, 100, 2000);
441
442 bufferevent_getwatermark(bev1, EV_WRITE, &low, &high);
443 tt_int_op(low, ==, 100);
444 tt_int_op(high, ==, 2000);
445
446 {
447 int r = bufferevent_getwatermark(bev1, EV_WRITE | EV_READ, &low, &high);
448 tt_int_op(r, !=, 0);
449 }
450
451 bufferevent_write(bev1, buffer, sizeof(buffer));
452
453 event_dispatch();
454
455 tt_int_op(test_ok, ==, 2);
456
457 /* The write callback drained all the data from outbuf, so we
458 * should have removed the write event... */
459 tt_assert(!event_pending(&bev2->ev_write, EV_WRITE, NULL));
460
461end:
462 if (bev1)
463 bufferevent_free(bev1);
464 if (bev2)
465 bufferevent_free(bev2);
466}

480/*
481 * Test bufferevent filters
482 */
483
484/* strip an 'x' from each byte */
485
486static enum bufferevent_filter_result
487bufferevent_input_filter(struct evbuffer *src, struct evbuffer *dst,
488 ev_ssize_t lim, enum bufferevent_flush_mode state, void *ctx)
489{
490 const unsigned char *buffer;
491 unsigned i;
492
493 buffer = evbuffer_pullup(src, evbuffer_get_length(src));
494 for (i = 0; i < evbuffer_get_length(src); i += 2) {
495 if (buffer[i] == '-')
496 continue;
497
498 assert(buffer[i] == 'x');
499 evbuffer_add(dst, buffer + i + 1, 1);
500 }
501
502 evbuffer_drain(src, i);
503 return (BEV_OK);
504}
505
506/* add an 'x' before each byte */
507
508static enum bufferevent_filter_result
509bufferevent_output_filter(struct evbuffer *src, struct evbuffer *dst,
510 ev_ssize_t lim, enum bufferevent_flush_mode state, void *ctx)
511{
512 const unsigned char *buffer;
513 unsigned i;
514 struct bufferevent **bevp = ctx;
515
516 ++test_ok;
517
518 if (test_ok == 1) {
519 buffer = evbuffer_pullup(src, evbuffer_get_length(src));
520 for (i = 0; i < evbuffer_get_length(src); ++i) {
521 evbuffer_add(dst, "x", 1);
522 evbuffer_add(dst, buffer + i, 1);
523 }
524 evbuffer_drain(src, evbuffer_get_length(src));
525 } else {
526 return BEV_ERROR;
527 }
528
529 if (bevp && test_ok == 1) {
530 int prev = ++test_ok;
531 bufferevent_write(*bevp, "-", 1);
532 /* check that during this bufferevent_write()
533 * bufferevent_output_filter() will not be called again */
534 assert(test_ok == prev);
535 --test_ok;
536 }
537
538 return (BEV_OK);
539}

541static void
542test_bufferevent_filters_impl(int use_pair, int disable)
543{
544 struct bufferevent *bev1 = NULL, *bev2 = NULL;
545 struct bufferevent *bev1_base = NULL, *bev2_base = NULL;
546 char buffer[8333];
547 int i;
548
549 test_ok = 0;
550
551 if (use_pair) {
552 struct bufferevent *xpair[2];
553 tt_assert(0 == bufferevent_pair_new(NULL, 0, xpair));
554 bev1 = xpair[0];
555 bev2 = xpair[1];
556 } else {
557 bev1 = bufferevent_socket_new(NULL, pair[0], 0);
558 bev2 = bufferevent_socket_new(NULL, pair[1], 0);
559 }
560 bev1_base = bev1;
561 bev2_base = bev2;
562
563 for (i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(buffer); i++)
564 buffer[i] = i;
565
566 bev1 = bufferevent_filter_new(bev1, NULL, bufferevent_output_filter,
567 BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE, NULL,
568 disable ? &bev1 : NULL);
569
570 bev2 = bufferevent_filter_new(bev2, bufferevent_input_filter,
571 NULL, BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE, NULL, NULL);
572 bufferevent_setcb(bev1, NULL, writecb, errorcb, NULL);
573 bufferevent_setcb(bev2, readcb, NULL, errorcb, NULL);
574
575 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_get_underlying(bev1), ==, bev1_base);
576 tt_ptr_op(bufferevent_get_underlying(bev2), ==, bev2_base);
577 tt_int_op(bufferevent_getfd(bev1), ==, -1);
578 tt_int_op(bufferevent_getfd(bev2), ==, -1);
579
580 bufferevent_disable(bev1, EV_READ);
581 bufferevent_enable(bev2, EV_READ);
582 /* insert some filters */
583 bufferevent_write(bev1, buffer, sizeof(buffer));
584
585 event_dispatch();
586
587 if (test_ok != 3 + !!disable)
588 test_ok = 0;
589
590end:
591 if (bev1)
592 bufferevent_free(bev1);
593 if (bev2)
594 bufferevent_free(bev2);
595
596}

608static void
609sender_writecb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *ctx)
610{
611 if (evbuffer_get_length(bufferevent_get_output(bev)) == 0) {
612 bufferevent_disable(bev,EV_READ|EV_WRITE);
613 TT_BLATHER(("Flushed %d: freeing it.", (int)bufferevent_getfd(bev)));
614 bufferevent_free(bev);
615 }
616}

618static void
619sender_errorcb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *ctx)
620{
621 TT_FAIL(("Got sender error %d",(int)what));
622}

630#define TEST_STR "Now is the time for all good events to signal for " \
631 "the good of their protocol"
632static void
633listen_cb(struct evconnlistener *listener, evutil_socket_t fd,
634 struct sockaddr *sa, int socklen, void *arg)
635{
636 struct event_base *base = arg;
637 struct bufferevent *bev;
638 const char s[] = TEST_STR;
639 TT_BLATHER(("Got a request on socket %d", (int)fd ));
640 bev = bufferevent_socket_new(base, fd, bufferevent_connect_test_flags);
641 tt_assert(bev);
642 bufferevent_setcb(bev, NULL, sender_writecb, sender_errorcb, NULL);
643 bufferevent_write(bev, s, sizeof(s));
644end:
645 ;
646}

648static int
649fake_listener_create(struct sockaddr_in *localhost)
650{
651 struct sockaddr *sa = (struct sockaddr *)localhost;
652 evutil_socket_t fd = -1;
653 ev_socklen_t slen = sizeof(*localhost);
654
655 memset(localhost, 0, sizeof(*localhost));
656 localhost->sin_port = 0; /* have the kernel pick a port */
657 localhost->sin_addr.s_addr = htonl(0x7f000001L);
658 localhost->sin_family = AF_INET;
659
660 /* bind, but don't listen or accept. should trigger
661 "Connection refused" reliably on most platforms. */
662 fd = socket(localhost->sin_family, SOCK_STREAM, 0);
663 tt_assert(fd >= 0);
664 tt_assert(bind(fd, sa, slen) == 0);
665 tt_assert(getsockname(fd, sa, &slen) == 0);
666
667 return fd;
668
669end:
670 return -1;
671}

673static void
674reader_eventcb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *ctx)
675{
676 struct event_base *base = ctx;
677 if (what & BEV_EVENT_ERROR) {
678 perror("foobar");
679 TT_FAIL(("got connector error %d", (int)what));
680 return;
681 }
682 if (what & BEV_EVENT_CONNECTED) {
683 TT_BLATHER(("connected on %d", (int)bufferevent_getfd(bev)));
684 bufferevent_enable(bev, EV_READ);
685 }
686 if (what & BEV_EVENT_EOF) {
687 char buf[512];
688 size_t n;
689 n = bufferevent_read(bev, buf, sizeof(buf)-1);
690 tt_int_op(n, >=, 0);
691 buf[n] = '\0';
692 tt_str_op(buf, ==, TEST_STR);
693 if (++n_strings_read == 2)
694 event_base_loopexit(base, NULL);
695 TT_BLATHER(("EOF on %d: %d strings read.",
696 (int)bufferevent_getfd(bev), n_strings_read));
697 }
698end:
699 ;
700}

717static void
718test_bufferevent_connect(void *arg)
719{
720 struct basic_test_data *data = arg;
721 struct evconnlistener *lev=NULL;
722 struct bufferevent *bev1=NULL, *bev2=NULL;
723 struct sockaddr_in localhost;
724 struct sockaddr_storage ss;
725 struct sockaddr *sa;
726 ev_socklen_t slen;
727
728 int be_flags=BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE;
729
730 if (strstr((char*)data->setup_data, "defer")) {
731 be_flags |= BEV_OPT_DEFER_CALLBACKS;
732 }
733 if (strstr((char*)data->setup_data, "unlocked")) {
734 be_flags |= BEV_OPT_UNLOCK_CALLBACKS;
735 }
736 if (strstr((char*)data->setup_data, "lock")) {
737 be_flags |= BEV_OPT_THREADSAFE;
738 }
739 bufferevent_connect_test_flags = be_flags;
740#ifdef _WIN32
741 if (!strcmp((char*)data->setup_data, "unset_connectex")) {
742 struct win32_extension_fns *ext =
743 (struct win32_extension_fns *)
744 event_get_win32_extension_fns_();
745 ext->ConnectEx = NULL;
746 }
747#endif
748
749 memset(&localhost, 0, sizeof(localhost));
750
751 localhost.sin_port = 0; /* pick-a-port */
752 localhost.sin_addr.s_addr = htonl(0x7f000001L);
753 localhost.sin_family = AF_INET;
754 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&localhost;
755 lev = evconnlistener_new_bind(data->base, listen_cb, data->base,
756 LEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE|LEV_OPT_REUSEABLE,
757 16, sa, sizeof(localhost));
758 tt_assert(lev);
759
760 sa = (struct sockaddr *)&ss;
761 slen = sizeof(ss);
762 if (regress_get_listener_addr(lev, sa, &slen) < 0) {
763 tt_abort_perror("getsockname");
764 }
765
766 tt_assert(!evconnlistener_enable(lev));
767 bev1 = bufferevent_socket_new(data->base, -1, be_flags);
768 bev2 = bufferevent_socket_new(data->base, -1, be_flags);
769 tt_assert(bev1);
770 tt_assert(bev2);
771 bufferevent_setcb(bev1, reader_readcb,NULL, reader_eventcb, data->base);
772 bufferevent_setcb(bev2, reader_readcb,NULL, reader_eventcb, data->base);
773
774 bufferevent_enable(bev1, EV_READ);
775 bufferevent_enable(bev2, EV_READ);
776
777 tt_want(!bufferevent_socket_connect(bev1, sa, sizeof(localhost)));
778 tt_want(!bufferevent_socket_connect(bev2, sa, sizeof(localhost)));
779
780 event_base_dispatch(data->base);
781
782 tt_int_op(n_strings_read, ==, 2);
783 tt_int_op(n_reads_invoked, >=, 2);
784end:
785 if (lev)
786 evconnlistener_free(lev);
787
788 if (bev1)
789 bufferevent_free(bev1);
790
791 if (bev2)
792 bufferevent_free(bev2);
793}

834static void
835want_fail_eventcb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *ctx)
836{
837 struct event_base *base = ctx;
838 const char *err;
839 evutil_socket_t s;
840
841 if (what & BEV_EVENT_ERROR) {
842 s = bufferevent_getfd(bev);
843 err = evutil_socket_error_to_string(evutil_socket_geterror(s));
844 TT_BLATHER(("connection failure on "EV_SOCK_FMT": %s",
845 EV_SOCK_ARG(s), err));
846 test_ok = 1;
847 } else {
848 TT_FAIL(("didn't fail? what %hd", what));
849 }
850
851 event_base_loopexit(base, NULL);
852}

855close_socket_cb(evutil_socket_t fd, short what, void *arg)
856{
857 evutil_socket_t *fdp = arg;
858 if (*fdp >= 0) {
859 evutil_closesocket(*fdp);
860 *fdp = -1;
861 }

864static void
865test_bufferevent_connect_fail(void *arg)
866{
867 struct basic_test_data *data = (struct basic_test_data *)arg;
868 struct bufferevent *bev=NULL;
869 struct event close_listener_event;
870 int close_listener_event_added = 0;
871 struct timeval one_second = { 1, 0 };
872 struct sockaddr_in localhost;
873 ev_socklen_t slen = sizeof(localhost);
874 evutil_socket_t fake_listener = -1;
875 int r;
876
877 test_ok = 0;
878
879 fake_listener = fake_listener_create(&localhost);
880 bev = bufferevent_socket_new(data->base, -1,
881 BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE | BEV_OPT_DEFER_CALLBACKS);
882 tt_assert(bev);
883 bufferevent_setcb(bev, NULL, NULL, want_fail_eventcb, data->base);
884
885 r = bufferevent_socket_connect(bev, (struct sockaddr *)&localhost, slen);
886 /* XXXX we'd like to test the '0' case everywhere, but FreeBSD tells
887 * detects the error immediately, which is not really wrong of it. */
888 tt_want(r == 0 || r == -1);
889
890 /* Close the listener socket after a second. This should trigger
891 "connection refused" on some other platforms, including OSX. */
892 evtimer_assign(&close_listener_event, data->base, close_socket_cb,
893 &fake_listener);
894 event_add(&close_listener_event, &one_second);
895 close_listener_event_added = 1;
896
897 event_base_dispatch(data->base);
898
899 tt_int_op(test_ok, ==, 1);
900
901end:
902 if (fake_listener >= 0)
903 evutil_closesocket(fake_listener);
904
905 if (bev)
906 bufferevent_free(bev);
907
908 if (close_listener_event_added)
909 event_del(&close_listener_event);
910}
911
912struct timeout_cb_result {
913 struct timeval read_timeout_at;
914 struct timeval write_timeout_at;
915 struct timeval last_wrote_at;
916 int n_read_timeouts;
917 int n_write_timeouts;
918 int total_calls;
919};
920
921static void
922bev_timeout_write_cb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)
923{
924 struct timeout_cb_result *res = arg;
925 evutil_gettimeofday(&res->last_wrote_at, NULL);
926}
927
928static void
929bev_timeout_event_cb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *arg)
930{
931 struct timeout_cb_result *res = arg;
932 ++res->total_calls;
933
934 if ((what & (BEV_EVENT_READING|BEV_EVENT_TIMEOUT))
935 == (BEV_EVENT_READING|BEV_EVENT_TIMEOUT)) {
936 evutil_gettimeofday(&res->read_timeout_at, NULL);
937 ++res->n_read_timeouts;
938 }
939 if ((what & (BEV_EVENT_WRITING|BEV_EVENT_TIMEOUT))
940 == (BEV_EVENT_WRITING|BEV_EVENT_TIMEOUT)) {
941 evutil_gettimeofday(&res->write_timeout_at, NULL);
942 ++res->n_write_timeouts;
943 }
944}
945
946static void
947test_bufferevent_timeouts(void *arg)
948{
949 /* "arg" is a string containing "pair" and/or "filter". */
950 struct bufferevent *bev1 = NULL, *bev2 = NULL;
951 struct basic_test_data *data = arg;
952 int use_pair = 0, use_filter = 0;
953 struct timeval tv_w, tv_r, started_at;
954 struct timeout_cb_result res1, res2;
955 char buf[1024];
956
957 memset(&res1, 0, sizeof(res1));
958 memset(&res2, 0, sizeof(res2));
959
960 if (strstr((char*)data->setup_data, "pair"))
961 use_pair = 1;
962 if (strstr((char*)data->setup_data, "filter"))
963 use_filter = 1;
964
965 if (use_pair) {
966 struct bufferevent *p[2];
967 tt_int_op(0, ==, bufferevent_pair_new(data->base, 0, p));
968 bev1 = p[0];
969 bev2 = p[1];
970 } else {
971 bev1 = bufferevent_socket_new(data->base, data->pair[0], 0);
972 bev2 = bufferevent_socket_new(data->base, data->pair[1], 0);
973 }
974
975 tt_assert(bev1);
976 tt_assert(bev2);
977
978 if (use_filter) {
979 struct bufferevent *bevf1, *bevf2;
980 bevf1 = bufferevent_filter_new(bev1, NULL, NULL,
981 BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE, NULL, NULL);
982 bevf2 = bufferevent_filter_new(bev2, NULL, NULL,
983 BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE, NULL, NULL);
984 tt_assert(bevf1);
985 tt_assert(bevf2);
986 bev1 = bevf1;
987 bev2 = bevf2;
988 }
989
990 /* Do this nice and early. */
991 bufferevent_disable(bev2, EV_READ);
992
993 /* bev1 will try to write and read. Both will time out. */
994 evutil_gettimeofday(&started_at, NULL);
995 tv_w.tv_sec = tv_r.tv_sec = 0;
996 tv_w.tv_usec = 100*1000;
997 tv_r.tv_usec = 150*1000;
998 bufferevent_setcb(bev1, NULL, bev_timeout_write_cb,
999 bev_timeout_event_cb, &res1);
1000 bufferevent_setwatermark(bev1, EV_WRITE, 1024*1024+10, 0);
1001 bufferevent_set_timeouts(bev1, &tv_r, &tv_w);
1002 if (use_pair) {
1003 /* For a pair, the fact that the other side isn't reading
1004 * makes the writer stall */
1005 bufferevent_write(bev1, "ABCDEFG", 7);
1006 } else {
1007 /* For a real socket, the kernel's TCP buffers can eat a
1008 * fair number of bytes; make sure that at some point we
1009 * have some bytes that will stall. */
1010 struct evbuffer *output = bufferevent_get_output(bev1);
1011 int i;
1012 memset(buf, 0xbb, sizeof(buf));
1013 for (i=0;i<1024;++i) {
1014 evbuffer_add_reference(output, buf, sizeof(buf),
1015 NULL, NULL);
1016 }
1017 }
1018 bufferevent_enable(bev1, EV_READ|EV_WRITE);
1019
1020 /* bev2 has nothing to say, and isn't listening. */
1021 bufferevent_setcb(bev2, NULL, bev_timeout_write_cb,
1022 bev_timeout_event_cb, &res2);
1023 tv_w.tv_sec = tv_r.tv_sec = 0;
1024 tv_w.tv_usec = 200*1000;
1025 tv_r.tv_usec = 100*1000;
1026 bufferevent_set_timeouts(bev2, &tv_r, &tv_w);
1027 bufferevent_enable(bev2, EV_WRITE);
1028
1029 tv_r.tv_sec = 0;
1030 tv_r.tv_usec = 350000;
1031
1032 event_base_loopexit(data->base, &tv_r);
1033 event_base_dispatch(data->base);
1034
1035 /* XXXX Test that actually reading or writing a little resets the
1036 * timeouts. */
1037
1038 /* Each buf1 timeout happens, and happens only once. */
1039 tt_want(res1.n_read_timeouts);
1040 tt_want(res1.n_write_timeouts);
1041 tt_want(res1.n_read_timeouts == 1);
1042 tt_want(res1.n_write_timeouts == 1);
1043
1044 test_timeval_diff_eq(&started_at, &res1.read_timeout_at, 150);
1045 test_timeval_diff_eq(&started_at, &res1.write_timeout_at, 100);
1046
1047end:
1048 if (bev1)
1049 bufferevent_free(bev1);
1050 if (bev2)
1051 bufferevent_free(bev2);
1052}
1053
1054static void
1055trigger_failure_cb(evutil_socket_t fd, short what, void *ctx)
1056{
1057 TT_FAIL(("The triggered callback did not fire or the machine is really slow (try increasing timeout)."));
1058}
1059
1060static void
1061trigger_eventcb(struct bufferevent *bev, short what, void *ctx)
1062{
1063 struct event_base *base = ctx;
1064 if (what == ~0) {
1065 TT_BLATHER(("Event successfully triggered."));
1066 event_base_loopexit(base, NULL);
1067 return;
1068 }
1069 reader_eventcb(bev, what, ctx);
1070}
1071
1072static void
1073trigger_readcb_triggered(struct bufferevent *bev, void *ctx)
1074{
1075 TT_BLATHER(("Read successfully triggered."));
1076 n_reads_invoked++;
1077 bufferevent_trigger_event(bev, ~0, bufferevent_trigger_test_flags);
1078}
1079
1080static void
1081trigger_readcb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *ctx)
1082{
1083 struct timeval timeout = { 30, 0 };
1084 struct event_base *base = ctx;
1085 size_t low, high, len;
1086 int expected_reads;
1087
1088 TT_BLATHER(("Read invoked on %d.", (int)bufferevent_getfd(bev)));
1089 expected_reads = ++n_reads_invoked;
1090
1091 bufferevent_setcb(bev, trigger_readcb_triggered, NULL, trigger_eventcb, ctx);
1092
1093 bufferevent_getwatermark(bev, EV_READ, &low, &high);
1094 len = evbuffer_get_length(bufferevent_get_input(bev));
1095
1096 bufferevent_setwatermark(bev, EV_READ, len + 1, 0);
1097 bufferevent_trigger(bev, EV_READ, bufferevent_trigger_test_flags);
1098 /* no callback expected */
1099 tt_int_op(n_reads_invoked, ==, expected_reads);
1100
1101 if ((bufferevent_trigger_test_flags & BEV_TRIG_DEFER_CALLBACKS) ||
1102 (bufferevent_connect_test_flags & BEV_OPT_DEFER_CALLBACKS)) {
1103 /* will be deferred */
1104 } else {
1105 expected_reads++;
1106 }
1107
1108 event_base_once(base, -1, EV_TIMEOUT, trigger_failure_cb, NULL, &timeout);
1109
1110 bufferevent_trigger(bev, EV_READ,
1111 bufferevent_trigger_test_flags | BEV_TRIG_IGNORE_WATERMARKS);
1112 tt_int_op(n_reads_invoked, ==, expected_reads);
1113
1114 bufferevent_setwatermark(bev, EV_READ, low, high);
1115end:
1116 ;
1117}

1234
1235struct bufferevent_filter_data_stuck {
1236 size_t header_size;
1237 size_t total_read;
1238};
1239
1240static void
1241bufferevent_filter_data_stuck_readcb(struct bufferevent *bev, void *arg)
1242{
1243 struct bufferevent_filter_data_stuck *filter_data = arg;
1244 struct evbuffer *input = bufferevent_get_input(bev);
1245 size_t read_size = evbuffer_get_length(input);
1246 evbuffer_drain(input, read_size);
1247 filter_data->total_read += read_size;
1248}
1249
1250/**
1251 * This filter prepends header once before forwarding data.
1252 */
1253static enum bufferevent_filter_result
1254bufferevent_filter_data_stuck_inputcb(
1255 struct evbuffer *src, struct evbuffer *dst, ev_ssize_t dst_limit,
1256 enum bufferevent_flush_mode mode, void *ctx)
1257{
1258 struct bufferevent_filter_data_stuck *filter_data = ctx;
1259 static int header_inserted = 0;
1260 size_t payload_size;
1261 size_t header_size = 0;
1262
1263 if (!header_inserted) {
1264 char *header = calloc(filter_data->header_size, 1);
1265 evbuffer_add(dst, header, filter_data->header_size);
1266 free(header);
1267 header_size = filter_data->header_size;
1268 header_inserted = 1;
1269 }
1270
1271 payload_size = evbuffer_get_length(src);
1272 if (payload_size > dst_limit - header_size) {
1273 payload_size = dst_limit - header_size;
1274 }
1275
1276 tt_int_op(payload_size, ==, evbuffer_remove_buffer(src, dst, payload_size));
1277
1278end:
1279 return BEV_OK;
1280}
1281
1282static void
1283test_bufferevent_filter_data_stuck(void *arg)
1284{
1285 const size_t read_high_wm = 4096;
1286 struct bufferevent_filter_data_stuck filter_data;
1287 struct basic_test_data *data = arg;
1288 struct bufferevent *xpair[2];
1289 struct bufferevent *filter = NULL;
1290
1291 int options = BEV_OPT_CLOSE_ON_FREE | BEV_OPT_DEFER_CALLBACKS;
1292
1293 char payload[4096];
1294 int payload_size = sizeof(payload);
1295
1296 memset(&filter_data, 0, sizeof(filter_data));
1297 filter_data.header_size = 20;
1298
1299 tt_assert(bufferevent_pair_new(data->base, options, xpair) == 0);
1300
1301 bufferevent_setwatermark(xpair[0], EV_READ, 0, read_high_wm);
1302 bufferevent_setwatermark(xpair[1], EV_READ, 0, read_high_wm);
1303
1304 tt_assert(
1305 filter =
1306 bufferevent_filter_new(xpair[1],
1307 bufferevent_filter_data_stuck_inputcb,
1308 NULL,
1309 options,
1310 NULL,
1311 &filter_data));
1312
1313 bufferevent_setcb(filter,
1314 bufferevent_filter_data_stuck_readcb,
1315 NULL,
1316 NULL,
1317 &filter_data);
1318
1319 tt_assert(bufferevent_enable(filter, EV_READ|EV_WRITE) == 0);
1320
1321 bufferevent_setwatermark(filter, EV_READ, 0, read_high_wm);
1322
1323 tt_assert(bufferevent_write(xpair[0], payload, sizeof(payload)) == 0);
1324
1325 event_base_dispatch(data->base);
1326
1327 tt_int_op(filter_data.total_read, ==, payload_size + filter_data.header_size);
1328end:
1329 if (xpair[0])

1331 if (filter)
